9 COMMITTEE SUBSTITUTE
10 An Act relating to professions and occupations;
amending 59 O.S. 2021, Section 1688, as amended by
11 Section 3, Chapter 355, O.S.L. 2024 (59 O.S. Supp.
2025, Section 1688), which relates to term of license
12 and registration certificates; prohibiting certain
expired license from being renewed; allowing certain
13 expired license to be reinstated; requiring certain
former licensee to submit certain application;
14 requiring certain application to include certain
information; exempting certain licensee from certain
15 continuing education requirements for certain time
period; requiring certain licensee to complete
16 certain continuing education requirement within
certain time period; updating statutory language; and
17 providing an effective date.
18
19
20 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
21 SECTION 1. AMENDATORY 59 O.S. 2021, Section 1688, as
22 amended by Section 3, Chapter 355, O.S.L. 2024 (59 O.S. Supp. 2025,
23 Section 1688), is amended to read as follows:
24
Req. No. 3879 Page 1

1 Section 1688. A. No license shall be issued for longer than
2 one (1) year, and all licenses shall expire on the last day in the
3 birth month of the licensee. A license may be renewed upon
4 application and payment of fees thirty (30) days preceding or
5 following the date the license is due. Licenses renewed more than
6 thirty (30) days following the date of expiration may be renewed
7 only upon application and payment of all required fees and payment
8 of any penalty for late renewal established by the Construction
9 Industries Board and upon compliance with any applicable continuing
10 education requirements established by the Board and the Electrical
11 License Act. No penalty for late renewal shall be charged to any
12 holder of a license which expires while the holder is in military
13 service, if an application for renewal is made within one (1) year
14 following the service discharge of the holder.
15 B. No journeyman or contractor license shall be renewed unless
16 the licensee has completed the required hours of continuing
17 education, pursuant to the Electrical License Act and as determined
18 and approved by the Committee of Electrical Examiners and approved
19 by the Construction Industries Board.
20 C. Any license that remains expired for longer than one (1)
21 year shall not be renewed but shall be reinstated pursuant to this
22 subsection when compliant with all license requirements. To obtain
23 the license formerly held, the former license holder shall be
24
Req. No. 3879 Page 2

1 requ ired to submit a reinstatement application provided by the Board
2 and either retest or satisfy all of the following:
3 1. Submit a complete reinstatement application to the Board;
4 2. Pay the standard license renewal fee and a reinstatement
5 penalty fee of Two Hundred Dollars ($200.00);
6 3. Submit certification of completion within the preceding
7 twelve-month period of all continuing education approved by the
8 Committee of Electrical Examiners as follows:
9 a. if the applicant has satisfied the continuing
10 education requirements required for license renewal
11 within the preceding thirty-six (36) months, no
12 additional continuing education shall be required, or
13 b. if the license has been expired for more than thirty-
14 six (36) months, the applicant shall complete twelve
15 (12) hours of continuing education for each full
16 thirty-six-month period the license has remained
17 expired, not to exceed twenty-four (24) hours; and
18 4. Submit an original sworn affidavit or other verification
19 satisfactory to the Board that the applicant has not been subject to
20 final disciplinary action that would preclude licensure and has not
21 been convicted of a crime that has a direct bearing on the
22 applicant’s fitness to practice as an electrician.
23
24
Req. No. 3879 Page 3

1 D. A licensee shall be exempt from the continuing education
2 requirements for license renewal for three (3) years from the date
3 the licensee passed his or her current licensing exam.
4 E. A licensee whose license was reinstated through the option
5 of completing the required hours of continuing education in lieu of
6 retesting after being expired for more than one (1) year shall, for
7 the first timely submitted license renewal of the reinstated
8 license, complete the continuing education required pursuant to this
9 section for renewing his or her license within thirty-six (36)
10 months beginning from the date of the last verified continuing
11 education course completed for reinstatement of an expired license.
12 F. An apprentice registration certificate shall be issued for
13 one (1) year, at which time the apprentice may reregister upon
14 meeting the requirements of the Construction Industries Board and
15 paying the renewal fee.
16 D. G. A student apprentice registration certificate shall be
17 issued for the registrant’s school year. A student apprentice
18 registration expires on the last day of the registrant’s school
19 year, at which time the apprentice may reregister upon meeting the
20 requirements of the Construction Industries Board and paying the
21 renewal fee.
22 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective November 1, 2026.
